{{other|Trading with the enemy (disambiguation)}}
'''Trading with the enemy''' is a legal term of English origin that is used with a number of related meanings. It refers to: #An offence at [[common law]] and under statute #A ground for condemnation of ships in [[Prize (law)|prize]] proceedings #A ground for illegality and nullity in contract<ref>McNair, Sir Arnold Duncan. Legal Effects of War. Second Edition. Cambridge University Press. 1944. Chapter 7.</ref>
==United Kingdom== The statutory offence is now created by section 1 of the [[Trading with the Enemy Act 1939]].
